1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,655
Start with the smallest unit of evaluation: a task.

2
00:00:03,605 --> 00:00:07,826
A task gives the AI Agent defined inputs and success criteria.

3
00:00:07,826 --> 00:00:13,663
One attempt at that task is a trial, and a collection of related tasks becomes an evaluation suite.

4
00:00:13,663 --> 00:00:17,644
The distinction matters because a vague request produces a vague score.

5
00:00:17,644 --> 00:00:24,461
If two domain experts cannot independently decide whether the task passed, the specification is not yet ready to measure.

6
00:00:24,461 --> 00:00:30,000
The Agent should know what it must produce, where the result belongs, and which constraints are essential.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,211
Next, separate the transcript from the outcome.

8
00:00:33,211 --> 00:00:39,086
The transcript records messages, tool calls, intermediate results, reasoning, and errors.

9
00:00:39,086 --> 00:00:42,990
The outcome is the final state left in the environment after the trial.

10
00:00:42,990 --> 00:00:47,173
For a booking Agent, “your flight is booked” appears in the transcript.

11
00:00:47,173 --> 00:00:50,384
The outcome is a valid reservation in the database.

12
00:00:50,384 --> 00:00:58,451
For a coding Agent, a convincing explanation is not the outcome; the changed repository, passing tests, and preserved behavior are.

13
00:00:58,451 --> 00:01:01,509
A grader scores one dimension of performance.

14
00:01:01,509 --> 00:01:07,855
It may check an exact state, apply a quality rubric, or ask a human expert to judge a subjective result.

15
00:01:07,855 --> 00:01:12,259
A task can use several graders because success is often multidimensional.

16
00:01:12,259 --> 00:01:15,250
Finally, remember what you are evaluating.

17
00:01:15,250 --> 00:01:17,894
An AI Agent is not only a model.

18
00:01:17,894 --> 00:01:22,442
The harness supplies instructions, tools, state, and orchestration.

19
00:01:22,442 --> 00:01:29,663
A weak tool contract or unstable environment can make the same model fail, so the model and harness must be evaluated together.

20
00:01:29,663 --> 00:01:34,240
First, define one task with explicit inputs and success criteria.

21
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:37,846
Second, separate the transcript from the final outcome.

22
00:01:37,846 --> 00:01:41,538
Third, evaluate the model and the Agent harness together.
